( see j. b. gough , charles the obscure , isis 70 , # 254 , pgs 576 - 579 )    charles and the robert brothers launched the world 's first ( unmanned ) hydrogen - filled balloon in august 1783 ; then in december 1783 , charles and his co - pilot nicolas - louis robert ascended to a height of about 1,800 feet ( 550 m ) in a manned balloon .

balloons : in 1783 jacques charles took flight no . 1 of a balloon filled with this gas , atomic no . 1

